    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-03-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-03-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="676"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d676">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 815.001 B 64/9.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-03-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 21, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The American Minister announces the death of President Bonilla and states that
                    Vice President Francisco Bertram has assumed the Presidency and informs the
                    Minister that the Cabinet Ministers will support him and no complications are
                    anticipated. The Minister has advised the American consulates and the Commander
                    of the American warships in Honduras.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
